Navigate to Azure Portal: Visit the Azure Portal website at https://portal.azure.com/.
Sign Up for Azure Account: If you don't have an Azure account, you'll need to sign up. If you have a Microsoft Account you can login through this account.Otherwise create an account.Click on the "Start free" or "Start" button depending on the offers available
Provide Account Information: You'll be asked to provide basic information such as your email address, country/region, and preferred language.
Verify your Identity: You'll need to verify your identity, usually through a verification code sent to your email or phone number.
Choose Subscription Type: Select the subscription type that best fits your needs. Azure offers various subscription options including Free Trial, Pay-As-You-Go, and others.
Provide Payment Information (if necessary): Depending on the subscription type you choose, you may need to provide payment information. Azure may require a credit card for identity verification purposes, even for free trials.
Access Azure Portal: Once your account is created and verified, you can log in to the Azure Portal using the credentials you provided during the sign-up process.
Explore Azure Services: After logging in, you'll have access to the Azure Portal dashboard where you can explore and manage various Azure services and resources.
Set Up Additional Security: Consider setting up additional security measures such as Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) to enhance the security of your Azure account.
Manage Subscriptions and Billing: Within the Azure Portal, you can manage your subscriptions, view usage and billing information, and adjust settings as needed.
Remember to keep your account credentials secure and follow best practices for managing your Azure resources to ensure the security and efficiency of your cloud services.
